  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency life- saving support to the most drought- affected pastoral and agro-pastoral households in Southwest State of Somalia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The objective of this $2m FAO project is to provide immediate access to basic household needs and ensure the survival of productive livestock during the drought period. With the CERF funding, FAO will provide unconditional cash to 25,200 Somalis for six months and water trucking services among the main livestock migratory routes, serving an estimated 45,000 animals owned by approximately 1,125 families. In total, FAO will target 31,956 persons, including 7,986 women and 8,312 girls.</narrative>
  </description>
